<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-800] inSyncReplica in Partition needs some tweaks</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-800</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. isUnderReplicated method in Partition.scala needs to take the leaderIsrUpdateLock before reading the inSyncReplica structure. We suspect that this could cause the gauge to read stale values from the cache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. toString api should take the leaderIsrUpdateLock to prevent anything from blowing up when it iterates the data structures&lt;/p&gt;</description>
