                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13599343" author="junrao" created="Mon, 11 Mar 2013 21:34:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, the leaderCount gauge in ReplicaManager needs to use the lock too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13600207" author="junrao" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 17:25:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch. Just one comment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. ReplicaManager: There is no need to sync on the leaderPartitionsLock to access allPartitions. It uses Pool, which is backed by a ConcurrentHashMap already.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13600276" author="nehanarkhede" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 18:12:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch, a few questions/comments -&lt;br/&gt;
ReplicaManager&lt;br/&gt;
1. Like Jun said, we don&apos;t need to synchronize on leaderPartitionsLock inside getOrCreatePartition and getPartition()&lt;br/&gt;
2. I don&apos;t think we need to synchronize on leaderPartitionsLock inside checkpointHighWatermarks too, that lock is protecting the leaderPartitions data structure.&lt;br/&gt;
3. In stopReplica(), we need to synchronize only around leaderPartitions, not allPartitions and the info statement following that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13600277" author="sriramsub" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 18:12:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You are right. I was being too paranoid there.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13600287" author="nehanarkhede" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 18:22:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on v2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13600288" author="nehanarkhede" created="Tue, 12 Mar 2013 18:22:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;v2 checked in&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
